itemData.name: 2024 Pokemon Paldea Adventure Chest
itemData.description: The Pokémon TCG: Paldea Adventure Chest is a must-have for any Pokémon Trading Card Game enthusiast. This adventure chest features a Paldea theme, with stunning artwork and designs that capture the essence of the Pokémon world. Inside the chest, you'll find a variety of Pokémon TCG cards, including booster packs, promo cards, and more. The Adventure Chest also includes a collector's guide to help you keep track of your collection. Whether you're a seasoned player or just starting out, the Pokémon TCG: Paldea Adventure Chest is the perfect addition to your Pokémon card collection.

itemData.name: Animal Colosseum Booster Pack - Animal Colosseum (EX05)
itemData.description:
Product Details
Contents:
Each booster pack contains 12 random cards.
The popular Four Sovereigns are included as ACE cards in this set. All four can be used as the key card when building a deck.
Huanglongmon, the embodiment of earth, is also included as a Digimon card for the first time. Look for 12 cards in the popular Deva category. Plus, Sayo and Koh from the Digimon Story game series also get cards for the first time.

Set Configuration: The Digimon: Animal Colosseum booster set includes a total of 74 possible cards - 26 Common, 20 Uncommon, 18 Rare, 8 Super Rare, and 2 Secret Rare.
Rarity:None
GTIN: 810059783461

itemData.name: Bandai | Dragon Ball Super CG: Starter Deck
itemData.description: The Bandai Dragon Ball Super CG Starter Deck - Fusion World (FS03) is a must-have for fans of the popular trading card game. This starter deck includes a ready-to-play deck with 51 cards, allowing players to jump right into the action. The deck is themed around Fusion World, adding an exciting twist to gameplay. With an included energy marker, play sheet, and alternative design card pack, this starter deck has everything you need to start playing. Suitable for ages 6 and up, this trading card game is perfect for two players and offers a playing time of approximately 30 minutes. Get ready to unleash your power and master the art of fusion with the Bandai Dragon Ball Super CG Starter Deck - Fusion World (FS03).

itemData.name: Blaine's Charizard Unlimited - Gym Challenge (G2)
itemData.description:
Product Details
Card Number / Rarity:002/132 / Holo Rare
Card Type / HP / Stage:Fire / 100 / Stage 2
Card Text:(1st and Normal Edition): Early prints of these cards have a Fighting-type symbol instead of the Fire-type symbol. Also, "Energy" is misspelled with a lowercase "e" instead of a capital "E".
Attack 1:[R] Roaring Flames (20+)
Discard all Fire Energy cards attached to Blaine's Charizard except 1. If all Energy cards attached to Blaine's Charizard provide 2 Fire Energy, discard all of them. This attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage for each Fire Energy discard in this way.
Attack 2:[RR] Flame Jet
Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokémon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)
Weakness / Resistance / Retreat Cost:W / F-30 / 3
Artist:Ken Sugimori
TCGplayer Tip:While later printings of Blaine's Charizard corrected the Fighting energy symbol to a Fire energy symbol, the first instance of the word "energy" remained lowercase in all printings. These errors have made Blaine's Charizard a hot commodity among collectors.

itemData.name: Celebrations Special Collection Pikachu V- Union (25th Anniv)
itemData.description: The Pokémon Celebrations Special Collection Pikachu V-UNION Card Game is a must-have for any fan of the franchise. This special collection features a single powerful Pokémon divided into four cards, which you can assemble from your discard pile with the help of Professor Burnet. Once assembled, Pikachu V-UNION brings four awesome attacks and impressive HP into battle. The collection also includes an oversize card showcasing Pikachu V-UNION as a single illustration, plus a handful of Pokémon TCG: Celebrations booster packs. With a playing time of 10+ minutes and designed for 2 players aged 6 and up, this card game is perfect for a fun new challenge. Can you put all the pieces together and become the ultimate Pokémon master?
